answers.body_markdown:
It has happen to me too.
As they say before Apache poi&#39;s HSSF produces *.xls files in binary BIFF format of Excel 97 - 2003. But the IFERROR function was introduced in Excel 2007. So HSSF cannot store IFERROR function properly. Only XSSF is able to do so since XSSF produces *.xlsx files in Office Open XML format of Excel 2007.

The solution I have found:
In the formula adding &quot;_xlfn.&quot; before the function that are give you an error.

In that case

    //PREVIOUS
    //c.setCellFormula(&quot;IFERROR(1/0,-1)&quot;);
    //
    //MODIFY TO
    c.setCellFormula(&quot;_xlfn.IFERROR(1/0,-1)&quot;);

As I have seen &quot;_xlfn.&quot; means that it is a formula that is not exist in that version and make it to no validate it in java and write it in the excel as you expect.

